            <title>[LU-8162] Get i_mutex lock when changing SUID bits</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8162</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;__generic_file_aio_write assumes i_mutex lock is taken.  We generally don&apos;t need it, as it&apos;s handled elsewhere in our stack, however on SLES_12, the condition is explicitly checked when changing the SUID bits and a stack is dumped (once per boot) to /var/log/messages&lt;/p&gt;</description>
